{"name":"write","arguments":{"path":"workspace/starfall/chapter-001.md","content":"# Chapter 1: The Falling Star

Celeste adjusted her telescope and gasped. A streak of light was heading for the Whispering Woods. The impact shook the ground. A crystal the size of a house glowed at the crater's center.
"}}

{"name":"write","arguments":{"path":"workspace/starfall/chapter-002.md","content":"# Chapter 2: The Star-Speaker

The crystal cracked. A figure stepped out. "I am the last Star-Speaker. Without me, the void will enter." Celeste felt a pull toward the crystal. It was choosing her.
"}}

{"name":"write","arguments":{"path":"workspace/starfall/chapter-003.md","content":"# Chapter 3: The Ascension

The Observatory Council arrived with guards. Celeste touched the crystal. "It is not a weapon. It is a gate. And I am its new key." She raised her hand and the stars answered.
"}}
